Acceptance criteria
By using TraceCovidPeopleAds you implicityly agree to the following Acceptance criteria which includes but is not limited to:
• Photographs are taken by TraceCovidPeopleAds. The use of Smartphone camera. All photographs submitted to TraceCovidPeopleAds either to Admin or via the TraceCovidPeopleAds App or any other means are the property of TraceCovidPeopleAds Admin and Developers and the author gives up all rights to the photograph. Any offensive material submitted to TraceCovidPeopleAds will be reported to the appropriate authority (in most cases the UK Police).
• TraceCovidPeopleAds captures GeoLocation X,Y coordinates. You approve of the location data reported by TraceCovidPeopleAds to be used in any way that the TraceCovidPeopleAds organisation or anyone you submit the data file produced by TraceCovidPeopleAds.
•  Any bug or issue reports submitted to TraceCovidPeopleAds are the sole property of TraceCovidPeopleAds and the user gives up all rights.
• Without exception, there is no time limit or other promise to fix bugs or issues.
•  Users of TraceCovidPeopleAds should be 21 or over. It is the users' responsibility to use the software and report bugs/issues via a person 21 years or older.
•  Any individual, company or group hoping, intending or actually using or processing the email or data file in any way must seek written permission to do so from the TraceCovidPeopleAds. Permission should be requested by using the ‘report issue’ email creation slider within the TraceCovidPeopleAds App.
•  TraceCovidPeopleAds should not be used in 'critical' situations and must not be relied on in a formal data capture or legal context.  TraceCovidPeopleAds should only be used as supplementary information because there are several places where the solution may not record data reliably - starting with user error and including but not limited to device capability, other Apps wiping saved data, email corruption, data corruption and so on. The Trace Task App should only be used for research purposes.
• TraceCovidPeopleAds saves data to your mobile device in a data file.
• You choose the recipients of an email with the data file attached. You are responsible for ensuring data conforms to data protection laws. 
• TraceCovidPeopleAds captures information about you, other people, organisations and locations using QR codes, photographs and data field entries.    You have the sole responsibility and authority to ensure data collected is in accordance with any data protection rights.
• TraceCovidPeopleAds' is provided free with advertisements in good faith, and in support of global research. Any data, in any form such as photographs or text, communicated from your device by any delivery mechanism (service, email for example) to the TraceCovidPeopleAds' organisation becomes the property of the TraceCovidPeopleAds - All rights and privileges passes to the TraceCovidPeopleAds' organisation. The TraceCovidPeopleAds' organisation may, at their discretion, choose to use all or any part of the data for their own or external purposes. The TraceCovidPeopleAds' organisation may transfer data rights to another person or organisation. Any data may be reported to an appropriate Authority if the data breaches or comes close to breaching unacceptabe behaviours or breeches in the Law. For example, photographs depicting inappropriate images will be sent to the Police.
• TraceCovidPeopleAds' organisation may change the TraceCovidPeopleAds App to collect and process data. You authorise the use of any or all of the data to be processed as part of a research or commercial activity.
